Rule 0: The DM is always correct, do not argue with the DMs.  If you have an issue, wait until later and speak with the Administration.
Rule 1: There is to be no undeclared PvP: You must have a valid reason to PvP with someone, you cannot walk up to them and stab them.  Stoppat
Rule 2: Joke characters will be removed and you will be required to remake: This includes characters with joke names or names from other popular series (No Harry Potters, no Solid Snakes, etc)
Rule 3: If you die in PVP you can NOT re-engage for 1 hour
Rule 4: Certain force powers are currently not working as intended, do not abuse force powers
Rule 5: Force Sense, finding force sensitive people, may ONLY be used if you have a valid reason to think that person is a force sensitive
Rule 6: Please do not take Force Sensitive feat, it's a wasted feat until you are a jedi or sith, at which point you're allowed to rebuild
Rule 7: Do not ask for Jedi and Sith, or any Force user.  There is an application, fill it out and you may be selected when a spot opens
Rule 8: Do not spam knockdown, called shot, disarm, etc.  Once per minute is enough usually
Rule 9: Keep Adult oriented RP out of public areas!
Rule 10: You must have a minimum of 5 levels in each class you take
Rule 11: Do not seriously injure, maim, torture, or otherwise do terrible things to another character unless permission is given by the character or a DM
Rule 12: If a DM is on as a player, please don't bother them.
Rule 13: All complaints should be accompanied by a screenshot.  Screenshot or it didn't happen.
Rule 14: Once jetpacks and force jump are out, please do not use them to jump over perma-locked doors or over interior walls
GENERAL BETA RULE: This server is still in beta, there are going to be issues and there are going to be things that are subject to change
We ask that you please keep this in mind, report anything wonky, and if you do something we don't like please remember we aren't doing anything to harm you, there was no rule against it but because we don't think it's fair we may add a rule against it.  Rules are subject to change, again it's not something we're doing against people, it's just part of the beta-process

Benjimen Aaron Germany

March 8, 1990 - June 27, 2009

To all of us Ben was a great friend who was there for you when you needed him. Whether it was to make you smile, laugh, or just help you understand things about Star Wars or NWN. To all of us he was a hell of a dm with his plots and events, and also as an ace mod builder.

It goes without saying that he will be missed by all of us. No one likes to hear when someone young dies, and it's even harder when it's your friend.

May he rest in peace with god above.

We love you Ben and we miss you....
      ....gone, but never forgotten.
